### ISSUE F-001: Broken Chunk Scheduler Concurrency Control (HIGH)

**File to modify**: `/repo/frontend/src/modules/files/chunk-scheduler.ts`

**Root cause**: Lines 115-121 use `Promise.race([pool[i].then(() => true), Promise.resolve(false)])` to detect settled promises. `Promise.resolve(false)` is already resolved and always wins the race against any `.then()` callback (which creates a new microtask), so `settled` is always `false` and no promises are ever spliced from the pool. The pool grows without bound, and `Promise.race(pool)` on line 113 resolves instantly once any single promise in the pool is done, providing no back-pressure.

**Fix**: Replace the `pool` array (lines 104-123) with a `Set`-based self-removing pattern. Each promise removes itself from the set upon settling, so `Promise.race` always waits on only genuinely outstanding work.

**Exact change** -- replace lines 104-127 with:

```typescript
    // Promise pool: process up to MAX_CONCURRENT_CHUNKS at a time
    const pool: Set<Promise<void>> = new Set();
    for (const index of pendingIndices) {
      if (this.isPaused) break;

      const promise = processNext(index).then(
        () => { pool.delete(promise); },
        () => { pool.delete(promise); },
      );
      pool.add(promise);

      if (pool.size >= MAX_CONCURRENT_CHUNKS) {
        await Promise.race(pool);
      }
    }

    // Wait for remaining
    await Promise.all(pool);
```

Key points:
- Change the type from `Promise<void>[]` to `Set<Promise<void>>`.
- The `.then()` / error handler on each promise deletes the promise from the set before `Promise.race` resolves its next caller.
- The variable `promise` is captured by the closure because `const` in the block scope makes the reference stable per iteration. The `.then()` callback runs after `pool.add(promise)` because `.then()` always runs asynchronously.
- Both the success and error paths call `pool.delete(promise)` so failed chunks do not leak in the pool.
- `await Promise.all(pool)` at the end ensures any remaining in-flight chunks complete (or throw).

**No other files need changes for this issue** -- the public API (`scheduleChunks`, `getActiveCount`, `pause`, `resume`) is unchanged.

