## Detailed Implementation Plan: Fix 3 High-Severity Findings

### Execution Order

1. **F-H1** (reservation auto-release) -- self-contained, low risk
2. **F-H3** (upload-new-version flow) -- creates chunks via the existing unencrypted pipeline
3. **F-H2** (chunk encryption) -- most invasive; changes how chunks are stored and retrieved everywhere

This ordering is correct because F-H2 changes the chunk storage format. Any code that creates chunks (including the new `uploadNewVersion` from F-H3) will need encryption added in F-H2. Doing F-H3 first lets us build the feature with the existing pipeline, then F-H2 adds encryption uniformly to all chunk write/read paths including the new version upload.

